Primary objective

Assist with the management, collection and validation of Australian Vocational Education and Training Management

Information Statistical Standard (AVETMISS) data and other relevant information.

Context statement

The VET Data team are the Department of Industry, Tourism and Trade’s vocational education and training (VET) reporting

unit. This team is responsible for the submission of data to national authorities, distribution of performance reports and the

provision of VET data advice and information.

Key duties and responsibilities

1. Coordinate the collection, evaluation and validation of data collected from Registered Training Organisations (RTOs) to

meet both national reporting and auditing requirements, and assist in grant contract management.

2. Undertake routine and responsive reporting and briefings to internal and external stakeholders including ministerial

briefings.

3. Provide advice on current and emerging issues and changes related to the collection and management of VET related

data.

4. Assist with the implementation of systems, processes and standards for the management and distribution of data.

5. Design and implement validation functions and processes to quality assure incoming VET data and related report outputs.

6. Provide mentoring, training, support and advice to clients and peers regarding VET data and related reporting

environments.

Selection criteria

Essential

1. Demonstrated experience managing data collections, including the ability to validate and manipulate data to generate

reports.

2. High-level analytical and problem solving skills with experience using SAS, Power BI and Microsoft SQL Server

applications.

3. Highly motivated with excellent interpersonal, oral and written communications skills, with a demonstrated ability to

present data and information to various audiences.

4. Demonstrated ability in developing processes that support the delivery of business objectives.

5. Proven ability to build and sustain strategic relationships with key stakeholders, interact effectively and work with people

of diverse cultures and backgrounds.

Desirable

1. Experience within the VET sector, in particular demonstrated experience working with the National AVETMIS Standards.

Company Profile

The Associate Data Analyst position will provide assistance to Pack Health’s operations and sales teams. They will support the development of a robust, best-in-class data model and identify innovative ways to drive better outcomes faster and more effectively. A strong desire to learn and a creative approach to problem solving is needed.

Specific Job Responsibilities include, but are not limited to:
• Ensuring success with external clients by:
• Ensuring deliverables (e.g., reports and presentations) are high quality
• Meeting with account managers to provide overviews of outcomes
• Managing project timelines to ensure timely delivery
• Supporting the development of a robust, best-in-class data model, by:
• Improving data processes to plug data gaps and improve quality
• Managing processes relating to data collection, cleansing, analyzing, and reporting
• Maintaining the data model and reporting to ensure ongoing quality (e.g., through KPIs)
• Identifying innovative ways to drive better outcomes faster and more effectively, by:
• Contributing to the development of Pack programs from a data perspective
• Contributing to the ongoing development of Pack Health’s outcomes framework
• Interpreting data in order to draw conclusions for managerial action and strategy
• Using statistical techniques for hypothesis testing to validate data and interpret results

QUALIFICATIONS

Required Education:
• Bachelor’s degree (Master’s degree preferred) in statistics, biostatistics, analytics, or health informatics

Skills:
• Experience with analysis software such as SPSS
• Experience with programming languages such as R, SQL
• Experience with data visualization such as Tableau, Looker
• Experience with healthcare data
• Have the ability to work collaboratively with teams within and external to the employer
• Must be comfortable working with a wide range of stakeholders and functional teams
• Excellent written and verbal communication skills for coordinating across teams

About the role:

The Tertiary Skills and Pathways team is responsible for the unit mapping project, as part of its program of work. Unit mapping uses natural language processing techniques to create a connection between tertiary education learning materials (VET and HE units), and skills taxonomies. Unit mapping helps to identify skills taught in tertiary education, and their potential relationship to occupations and the labour market, to assist in analysis and advice on tertiary education delivery.

The team is working on a demonstration project basis with five key projects to design the end to end process of unit mapping, to continually refine the data science model, and to generate insights on the potential use of mapping outputs. The outputs of models are large, for example one university with approximately 3,000 units can have an output of approximately 30,000 skills mapped. Validation of outputs is a critical part of the mapping process to produce a model and results that are highly accurate.

Duties:
• Developing of a comprehensive internal and external validation process for very large data sets, to support improvement of data science models, and the quality of output data sent to partners. This may require an ensemble of approaches, for example statistical sampling, manual and automated approaches to validation.
• Managing internal validation processes before outputs are sent to project partners.
• Working closely with the data science team to provide feedback for the mapping model development.
• Analysing complex model outputs, to derive valuable insights for reporting to project partners, including visualisation techniques.
• Providing advice to technical services on interface design for a validation application for project partners.

Required experience/skills:
• Demonstrated experience in data analysis and process design, to create replicable data validation processes to improve data output quality.
• Excellent analytical skills, with strong attention to detail, and the ability to synthesise and critically analyse large volumes of structured and unstructured data.
• Strong skills and experience in data management, in particular how data can be effectively structured, analysed, presented and communicated, to achieve high-quality outcomes.
• Excellent communication skills, including the ability to effectively communicate key data insights visually and in written form to a range of diverse stakeholders
• Well-developed interpersonal skills, including the ability to work effectively in a multidisciplinary setting.

Desirable experience skills:
• Experience in R Shiny, Python, SQL, anduser experience design.
• Understanding of, and experience working with tertiary education (HE and/or VET) and/or occupation and labour market data.
• Understanding and experience in data science, or related fields.
• Experience operating in a policy environment.

For thousands of years, maps have provided humans with the knowledge they need to make decisions. As a Maps Data Analyst, you will have the opportunity to provide ground truth for your town, city or country.

At Peroptyx, we are looking for Data Analysts who will review mapping data for digital mapping applications. Your research capabilities will validate and ensure that the navigation of certain routes are accurate and safe.

As part of this role you will verify that business names and opening hours are correct. You will check that the distance from a starting point to an end destination is listed accurately resulting in better user experiences.

With this job you can plan your days around this highly flexible working schedule, work weekends or late evenings, all from the comfort of your own office. The flexibility of our roles minimizes the impact on your daily routine.

So, whether you are a student looking to earn as you learn, a retiree looking for a new challenge a part-time/full time professional or a work from home parent, Peroptyx has the right role for you

Ideal Candidate
• Fluent in English.
• Excellent research skills.
• Excellent local knowledge of your home country.
• Good understanding and general knowledge of the geography and culture of Australia.
• Analytical mindset.

Job Requirements
• Must be living in Australia for a minimum of 5 consecutive years.
• Must pass an online open-book exam that can verify your full understanding of the material and concepts.
• Must be willing to work a minimum of 10 hours and up to 20 hours per week depending on task availability.
• Good working knowledge of search engines, map applications and familiarity with social media platforms.
• Strong ability to learn, understand and apply multiple sets of different instructions.
• All work must be of an independent nature.

Technical requirements to perform the work

Access to a laptop or computer which uses:
- A logon account unique to you
- Anti-virus solution that is kept up to date, with regular scans performed
- Only one member per household may apply
NB. All products should be provided at your own expense.

Benefits

· Work up to 20 hours per week.
· Earn a competitive rate of pay.
· Develop your research skills.
· Avoid the long commute.
· Work from the comfort of your home office.
· Enjoy the flexibility of setting your own working hours

Analyse and improve business processes in relation to the student experience at CDU

About the Position

As the Business Analyst (Student Systems) , you will analyse and work to continually improve business processes and practices in relation to the student experience.

Working closely with subject matter experts, University business units, stakeholders, and vendors in the elicitation of business requirements your duties will include :
• Analysis of business processes and systems that impact on the way staff and students interact with student systems.
• Business process mapping and implementing business process improvements across business units.
• Problem identification, requirements elicitation and solution design
• Incident management and coordination of user acceptance testing
• Security, training, access, and support
• Operating within an Agile project management environment that requires a broad understanding of ICT technologies, customer experience and business analysis methodologies.

About You

To be successful, you will require :
• Demonstrated project management skills and commitment to continuous improvement of processes and personal drive and self-motivation.
• Demonstrated knowledge of business process improvement methodologies and ability to apply them across teams.
• Demonstrated experience in conducting training, testing, and ability to manage systems access requirements within a role-based security model.
• Verbal communication skills, with the ability to communicate complex processes or regulations, to provide clear information to customers and to communicate effectively with staff.
• Written communication skills, with the ability to document business processes, guidelines and work instructions and develop training material for administrative staff.
• Advanced level of technical proficiency in administrative systems and platforms, including the use of large corporate databases and MSOffice software.
• Subject matter expertise in one or more fields of VET and / or HE student and academic administration and the legislation and regulation that governs it.
• Experience in leading lean (or similar) business process improvement projects or programs of work.

To view the responsibilities of the role, please click on the : Position Profile.

Remuneration

Appointment to this role will be at Professional Level 6 / 7. The base salary will be in the range of $83,265 - $98,622 per annum.

The total remuneration package will be in the range of $97,420 - $115,387 per annum, including 17% superannuation.

What’s in it for you?
• An employer who values your contribution to building a bigger, better and stronger university
• Work with a University committed to changing people’s lives for the better through training, education and research
• Opportunities for professional development, paid study and career progression
• An enviable lifestyle in the spectacular Northern Territory
• Generous relocation assistance
• 17% superannuation
• Six weeks of paid annual leave
• Up to 26 weeks of paid parental leave (primary care giver), in addition to government payments (eligibility criteria apply)
• Recognition of prior service with another Australian University / NT Government for Long Service Leave (recognition applied to qualifying period only)
• Ability to negotiate transfer of leave entitlements under the Public Employment (Mobility) Act 1989
• Free on-campus parking in designated areas
• Employee Assistance Program
• Salary Packaging opportunities

How to Apply

All applications must be received online via the apply’ button and should include your resume and a cover letter outlining your interest in the role and relevant skills and experience.

For a confidential discussion about the position please contact Cara Gordon on 08 8946 6456 or email cara.gordon@cdu.edu.au

Adjustments can be made throughout the application and selection process, as well as during employment to support applicants and employees with disability.

CDU’s Workplace Adjustment Policy and Procedure can be found at https : / / policies.cdu.edu.au / view-current.php?id 191&version 1.

If you would like to discuss adjustments, please contact the Recruitment Team on 08 8946 6492 or email strategicrecruitment@cdu.edu.au.

Diversity and Inclusion

At CDU we actively celebrate our diversity. We innovate, embrace new ideas, and act with courage and kindness. We’re about what we can give to the world rather than what we take, and we believe in the transformative power of education.

We work hard to make sure every member of our University community feels they truly belong. Understanding that it is through our focus on our people and leveraging our differences that will make CDU the most connected university in Australia, we are striving to ensure that our culture and our community are inclusive of all our staff, students and visitors.

We are committed to maintaining a culture where everyone feels respected, safe, encouraged to speak up and supported in achieving their professional goals.

Applications from First Nations people, women at all levels, culturally and linguistically diverse people, people with disability, neurotypical and neurodiverse people, LGBTIQ+ people, people with family and caring responsibilities and people at all stages of their careers are welcomed.

You make CDU. And we want you to be exactly who you are.

BA required for development of custom .NET Revenue Management System build including design, development, testing and implementation activities.

The Business Analyst will be part of a BA team integral to the development of a custom .NET Revenue Management System build including design, development, testing and implementation activities.

The successful applicant will be required to be based in Darwin for the duration of the contract.

Key Duties and Responsibilities

• Undertake analysis of a revenue management business subject matter

• Maintain a professional relationship with project resources, and the project customer

• Participate in analysis and design related workshops to inform user story creation

• Participate in other related workshops such as sprint planning and oversight

• Developing user stories

• Utilisation of project tool sets such as Onenote, SharePoint, MS Teams, Jira and Confluence

• Process design and re-engineering

• Business impact and gap analysis

• Workshop facilitation

• Workflow automation

• Work calmly in a sometimes ambiguous environment setting

• Highly effective client liaison interpersonal skills

• Demonstrated experience in being able to provide a holistic, human centred approach to the design of digital products, defining their form, behaviour, and content, drawing on a range of skills encompassing user research; interface, interaction and information design; project and time management, technical writing and usability testing.

• Demonstrated experience working in a collaborative environment with high performing teams with high priority deliverables under tight timeframes, and balancing competing priorities.

• Hands on experience in the end to end delivery of major business systems projects

• Highly skilled in the use of BA related tools such as MS Visio and Balsamiq

Desirable Skills and Experience

• High level understanding of probability and statistics

Personal Qualities required of Candidate

• High level social and written skills with the ability to effectively communicate with team members and stakeholders, including ability to translate complex analytical and technical information into clear and meaningful terms.

• Ability to work in a small team environment with members of diverse cultures and backgrounds and differing skill sets.

• Self-starter with high personal drive and a positive attitude.

• Behaves in a respectful and professional manner, maintaining high integrity and transparency at all times during the project.

• Excellent problem solver and critical thinker.

About Alooba

Hello! We are Alooba - a skills assessment platform for analytics, data science & data literacy. Our customers use us to better understand their people and their job candidates. We are like the ‘Moneyball’ of hiring, helping businesses focus on the things that matter and removing those that don’t. The result? A fairer, cheaper, faster and more accurate hiring process that focuses on the skills needed for the job. Our vision is to create a world where everyone can get the job they deserve. Can you help us achieve that?

Our culture is very important to us. We value no-nonsense people who use common sense to get sh!t done and make it happen. You’ll put our users first, and focus on improving our product and yourself every day. You’ll be able to straddle the need to work very fast and push stuff live, while maintaining a high standard and taking care of the details. You really must care, and this can’t just be ‘a job’ for you. And when work time is over, it’s party time!

Our hiring process always starts with a fair, skills-based quiz on our platform, customised for the role. This will help us both understand your skills, ensure everyone is treated fairly and you’ll get a chance to see what you’ll be building. If you ace the quiz, you’re guaranteed an interview. No matter what happens, you’ll see your score at the end of the quiz.

We are, genuinely, an equal opportunity employer. We also don’t care about things that traditionally appear on job ads like ‘years of experience’, university qualifications etc.

The Role

We currently have a small team of remote developers, however we’re looking to set up our core development office in Sydney at Fishburners. We’re looking for a set of strong senior software engineers to help bring our product to the next level, with a major overhaul of the system architecture, using a service oriented approach and expanding our feature set.

You should have experience building well structured systems and are keen to work in the fast paced startup environment with a drive to do whatever it takes to make it happen. As we are still a small company, you will have a direct impact on the success of the business. You will be the driving force behind the implementation of the features and functionalities you’ll be working on.

You will work directly with the CTO, founder and a small team of developers to build out our assessment platform to be an enterprise grade web application to serve our small but growing user-base spread across the world.

Our application is built with PHP (Laravel/Lumen), PostgreSQL, and React.js and is running on AWS. We are looking for capable people that can help expand our product and build it to scale with our users. You will be responsible for designing, developing, testing and maintaining the application and supporting services.

Responsibilities
• Take ownership of features and functionality and see it through from conceptualisation to productionisation
• Design and develop highly scalable, and maintainable code
• Design and develop system database schemas and RESTful API interfaces
• Thoroughly test new functionalities and existing systems
• Manage infrastructure as code and utilize CI/CD pipelines

Benefits
• Unlimited opportunities to grow your skill set in a fast-paced startup environment.
• No corporate bureaucracy, red tape, endless meetings and other big company nonsense - work directly with the CTO and founder on a daily basis.
• 5 days paid learning leave per year.
• Competitive salary and share options.
• The chance to get in early on the next big thing, and leave your legacy.

• Attention to detail
• Ability to understand and interpret user needs

• Solid understanding of Object-Oriented Programming principles and patterns
• Solid understanding of Relational Databases and SQL
• Strong communication skills
